.TH RPG 1 "March 2026" "rpg 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rpg \- Terminal-based RPG to-do list and task management system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rpg
[\fIOPTION\fR] [\fIARGUMENTS...\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B RPG To-Do List
is a productivity tool that gamifies your daily task management. By completing tasks, you earn Experience Points and in-game currency. When executed without any arguments, it launches the interactive menu.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display this help and exit.
.TP
.BR \-ta ", " \-\-task\-add " \fI""TASK_NAME"" HARDNESS AUTO_CALC\fR"
Add a new task to the system. If the task name contains spaces, it must be enclosed in double quotes.
.br
\fIHARDNESS\fR: An integer between 1 and 5.
.br
\fIAUTO_CALC\fR: 1 to let the system calculate rewards based on hardness, 0 for manual assignment.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-complete " \fI""TASK_NAME""\fR"
Successfully complete the specified task. The system will reward the user's profile with EXP and Gold based on the task's difficulty, and the task will be archived.
.TP
.BR \-ctp ", " \-\-change\-task\-parameters " \fI""TASK_NAME"" PARAM_ID ""NEW_VALUE""\fR"
Update the parameters of an existing task.
.br
\fIPARAM_ID Values\fR:
.br
  1: Task Name
.br
  2: Hardness Level
.br
  3: Reward (Gold)
.br
  4: Experience Points (EXP)
.br
  5: Task Details
.TP
.BR \-sf ", " \-\-show\-finished
List the history of all completed and archived tasks.
.TP
.BR \-dt ", " \-\-delete\-task " \fI""TASK_NAME""\fR"
Permanently delete the specified task from the system without granting any rewards or EXP.
.TP
.BR \-qa ", " \-\-quit\-account
Log out of the current session. If auto-login is active, this will disable it and return to the authentication screen.
.SH EXAMPLES
Add a new task with a hardness of 4 and auto-calculated rewards:
.PP
.RS
$ rpg -ta "task_name" 4 1
.RE
.PP
Claim the reward for a completed task:
.PP
.RS
$ rpg -c "task_name"
.RE
.PP
Change the hardness level (Parameter 2) of an existing task to 5:
.PP
.RS
$ rpg -ctp "task_name" 2 "5"
.RE
.SH AUTHOR
Written by the RPG To-Do List Developer.
